Here's a comprehensive list of Docker components and concepts, organized by category.
Core Architecture

Docker Engine — the core runtime
Docker Daemon (dockerd) — background service managing objects
Docker Client (docker CLI) — command-line interface
REST API — interface between client and daemon
containerd — high-level container runtime
runc — low-level OCI runtime
shim (containerd-shim) — keeps containers running independent of daemon

Core Objects

Image — read-only template for containers
Container — runnable instance of an image
Volume — persistent data storage
Network — container connectivity
Registry — image storage/distribution (Docker Hub, etc.)
Repository — collection of related images (tags)
Tag — image version label

